<HL>
   Viacom Class B Stock Cleared
</HL>
<DATE>
05/25/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C17
</SO>
<CO>
   VIA
</CO>
<IN>
DIVIDENDS (DIV)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- Viacom Inc. shareholders approved the creation
of 150 million shares of Class B nonvoting common stock to
allow the entertainment company greater flexibility in
acquisitions. A total of 53.4 million Class B shares -- one
for each common share outstanding -- will be issued and
distributed as a dividend on June 13 to stock of record June
6, and will trade on the American Stock Exchange under the
symbol VIAB.
   ---
</LP>
<TEXT>
